---
import BaseLayout from '@components/base/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Trip Planner - Washington Hot Springs"
  description="Plan your perfect hot springs road trip with custom itineraries, drive times, and route optimization."
>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4 text-center">Hot Springs Trip Planner</h1>
      
      <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <p class="text-lg text-center mb-6">
          Create custom itineraries, optimize routes, and discover the perfect hot springs adventure for your timeline and interests.
        </p>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-8">
          <div class="text-center p-4 rounded-lg bg-dark-2/50">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-2">🗺️</div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Interactive Map</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">View all springs, get directions, and see drive times</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 rounded-lg bg-dark-2/50">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-2">⏱️</div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Drive Time Zones</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">See what's reachable from any city in 30 min to 3 hours</p>
          </div>
          <div class="text-center p-4 rounded-lg bg-dark-2/50">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-2">🛂</div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2">Passport Tracking</h3>
            <p class="text-sm">Track visited springs and earn badges</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="text-center">
          <a 
            href="/washington-hot-springs-map" 
            class="btn btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-3"
          >
            Open Full Map & Planner →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Featured Itineraries -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Featured Itineraries</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <!-- The Rainier-to-Gorge Loop -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Rainier-to-Gorge Loop</h3>
            <p class="mb-4 text-gray-300">A perfect 3-day weekend combining old-growth forest soaks, historic resort baths, and alpine wilderness.</p>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 1: Mount Rainier National Park</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Soak at <a href="https://washingtonhotsprings.com/blog/ohanapecosh-hot-springs" class="text-primary hover:underline">Ohanapecosh Hot Springs</a> under old-growth canopy. Camp at nearby Cougar Rock or stay at Paradise Inn.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 2: White Pass to Columbia Gorge</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Drive the scenic White Pass Byway to <a href="https://washingtonhotsprings.com/blog/carson-hot-springs-complete-visitor-guide" class="text-primary hover:underline">Carson Hot Springs</a> for a historic stone soak with Gorge views. Overnight in Stevenson or Carson.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 3: North Cascades Alpine Soak</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Return via <a href="https://washingtonhotsprings.com/blog/baker-hot-springs-washington-state" class="text-primary hover:underline">Baker Hot Springs</a> for a final alpine soak before heading home.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-lg bg-dark-2/30">
              <p class="text-sm"><strong>Total Distance:</strong> ~280 miles | <strong>Best Season:</strong> Late spring through early fall | <strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy to Moderate</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Olympic Peninsula Circuit -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Olympic Peninsula Circuit</h3>
            <p class="mb-4 text-gray-300">A diverse 4-5 day adventure combining coastal rainforest, mountain views, and island escapes.</p>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 1: Sol Duc Valley</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Soak at Sol Duc Hot Springs Resort in Olympic National Park, then explore the surrounding rainforest trails.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 2: Olympic Coast</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Drive to the coast and explore the beaches, then head to Lake Quinault for evening soaking.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 3: Ferry to Orcas Island</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Take the ferry from Anacortes to Orcas Island for <a href="https://washingtonhotsprings.com/blog/doe-bay-hot-spring" class="text-primary hover:underline">Doe Bay Hot Spring</a> - ocean views and island relaxation.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 4: Island Exploration</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Explore Orcas Island's hiking trails, waterfalls, and beaches before your return soak at Doe Bay.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-lg bg-dark-2/30">
              <p class="text-sm"><strong>Total Distance:</strong> ~350 miles + ferry | <strong>Best Season:</strong> Summer and early fall | <strong>Difficulty:</strong> Easy</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- The Glacier Peak Wilderness Challenge -->
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Glacier Peak Wilderness Challenge</h3>
            <p class="mb-4 text-gray-300">A strenuous 3-day backpacking adventure for experienced hikers seeking remote wilderness soaks.</p>
            
            <div class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 1: Trek to Goldmyer</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Hike 4.5 miles to <a href="https://washingtonhotsprings.com/blog/goldmyer-hot-springs" class="text-primary hover:underline">Goldmyer Hot Springs</a> through old-growth forest. Camp at designated wilderness sites.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 2: Deep Wilderness</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Continue to <a href="https://washingtonhotsprings.com/blog/gamma-hot-springs" class="text-primary hover:underline">Gamma Hot Springs</a> - a challenging 10-mile hike to one of Washington's most remote soaks.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              
              <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-semibold">Day 3: Return Journey</h4>
                  <p class="text-gray-300">Hike out via the Suiattle River Trail, celebrating your wilderness achievement.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="mt-6 p-4 rounded-lg bg-dark-2/30">
              <p class="text-sm"><strong>Total Distance:</strong> ~30+ miles hiking | <strong>Best Season:</strong> Late summer | <strong>Difficulty:</strong> Strenuous - Expert hikers only</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Planning Tips -->
      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">Planning Tips</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-2xl mr-3">📅</span> Seasonal Considerations
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li><strong>Summer (June-Aug):</strong> Best for high-elevation springs, but most crowded</li>
              <li><strong>Fall (Sept-Oct):</strong> Ideal temperatures, fewer crowds, stunning foliage</li>
              <li><strong>Winter (Nov-Mar):</strong> Many mountain springs inaccessible due to snow</li>
              <li><strong>Spring (Apr-May):</strong> Snow melt makes some areas muddy but accessible</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-2xl mr-3">🎒</span> What to Bring
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>Multiple swimsuits (they stay damp)</li>
              <li>Quick-dry towels and sandals</li>
              <li>Plenty of water and snacks</li>
              <li>First aid kit and navigation tools</li>
              <li>Protection for electronics from steam</li>
              <li>Headlamp for evening soaks</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-2xl mr-3">🚗</span> Transportation
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>AWD/4WD recommended for forest roads</li>
              <li>Check road conditions before departure</li>
              <li>Download offline maps - cell service is spotty</li>
              <li>Carry chains in winter months</li>
              <li>EV charging stations marked on our map</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="glass rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-2xl mr-3">🏕️</span> Accommodation
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
              <li>Campgrounds marked on the map</li>
              <li>Hot springs resorts offer lodging</li>
              <li>Nearby towns have hotels/motels</li>
              <li>Backcountry camping requires permits</li>
              <li>Book popular spots in advance</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Call to Action -->
      <div class="glass rounded-lg p-8 text-center">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Start Planning?</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-6 text-gray-300">
          Use our interactive map to build your custom route, check current conditions, and track your progress.
        </p>
        <a 
          href="/washington-hot-springs-map" 
          class="btn btn-primary text-xl px-10 py-4 inline-block"
        >
          Open Trip Planner Map →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
